You work as the IT staff in a company, a new intern Sam started today.You received an email from HR to create Sam in the system with all the necessary credentials.
Create user Sam
Give Sam password Sam#123
Create group interns
Add Sam to the interns group 
Grant group interns read only priviledges to the /tmp folder your created in Day4
NB: Kindly outline the steps you took to finish this task.

STEPS TAKEN
I used the command, <sudo adduser sam> to create a secure account for the intern and ensure proper system access control.
I used the command, <sudo passwd sam> to set password,  Sam#123 , for sam

I created the group, interns using the command,  <sudo groupadd interns>
I used the command, <getent group interns> to confirm if the group, interns was created.

I used the command, <sudo usermod -aG interns sam> to add sam to the interns group
Importance: Grants Sam access to shared resources assigned to the interns group. The -aG is very important:
•	-a = append (keeps existing groups)
•	-G = specify group
I used the command, <id sam> to verify if sam was added to the interns group.
I used <sudo chown :interns tmp >to change the group ownership to interns.
I used the command, < sudo chmod 750 tmp> to give read & execute permission to the group, interns. 
•	7 → Owner = read, write, execute
•	5 → Group (interns) = read, execute (read-only access)
•	0 → Others = no access

Group was give execute permission because Folders need execute (x) permission to be opened/accessed.
I used the command, <ls –ld> to confirm the permission
I ran <git add Day5> command to stage Day5 file
I ran <git commit -m "Create a New User, Sam"> to commit Day5 file
I used <git push> to push the file to my remote repo on github


